glitter and they will yet shine silently on. <br><br>Choking in trampled upheaval, on gore of bits of fair flesh and their own swathe of bloody conflict, ever nameless, is a sacred memory: see, here yip's the stricken grass, and witness over there, stunted Oaks. These things know.    <br><br>For beneath there some dark forbidden death is laid in the precious soil. That unalterable stench does not ever fade away. <br><br>Enchantment, ennervating ripples of its magical power linger preserving something of this ancient leafy sanctuary yet, which stood here: glad memories to fill you, a wandering passerby, with renewed satisfactory vitality that grows, and blooms to life, and mushroomed here the wise Ages long ago into a leaping forest of uncanny wilderness. Up into birdsong far beyond the eye. <br><br>Time paced the long while here since, upon this ground, and the green citadel slowly yielded unwilling to sup on that dark forbidden stain. It did become sickly, yellowing in both blade and respectful leaf: where no shadow before yet fell. Though Fire has scorched the forest and dunes creep over it. Something remains. An evil loosed Sorrow into this wan verdure and in its quarrel gives this tale there. <br><br>Harken thou upon these words, O Wanderer! This ground is the old glen of bright Elven home's ancient forest door. <br><br>[more to come]    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/eq12.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/12/02 7:21:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/24/01