sty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/eq12.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/12/02 5:51:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/26/01 10:00:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Title: the next chance just beside an opportunity</span><hr size=1> At his side hung a great sword.  Its pommel was long, suggesting a double handed grip, its scabbard fretted with gems and inlaid chased Ivory.  Imladrisel, he was called, for the sword was blessed.<br><br>&quot;You seem silent, my old friend, ..&quot; mused the fellow.  &quot;See, already friends come nigh. Here are no foes.&quot; He spoke as if the words were given to somebody standing beside him, but he patted the great sword. <br><br>The touch ignited a sudden fiery light springing forth within blessed Imladrisel. Intense brilliance shining from depths inside the scabbard that reached all along the length of the blade to the sword tang, and pommel grip. The wise veteran could only shade his shocked stare, blinded at this sight. His reeling sensibility now seemed to feel Imladrisel' unnaturally stir, writhe wildly from wakened rest to rise unsheathed at a mere touch. <br><br>Upon his ears its sound rang out, unmistakably crying hot rage as clear as a scream of an Eagle, and to his staggered amazement Windshoal saw that he beheld a Holy Sword of great Takish Hiz answering truly, at last. There in front of him stood Imladrisel.  <br>   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/eq12.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/11/02 1:25:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/28/01 6:43:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Title: the next chance just beside an opportunity</span><hr size=1> "What might this strange wonder signify?" came from his lips, Windshoal heard himself speak these words across a great distance. He had returned again to this place to search for a meaning there, when Imladrisel spoke to him with this sign. Much was afoot that he did not understand. <br><br>Such a sign held within it terrible meaning, he understood its was a protest, against evil, implicitly: a great wrong must cause to him this unearthly summons. Again he trembled in fear, for the thought occurred to him now that he was called by The Lady Tunare to oppose some nameless quarrel of heaven, unaided. Yet he also dared not to set aside this doubt for obviously his fearsome enemy must lay somewhere ahead. Reason enough to tremble. <br><br>He barely finished considering anew the matters Imladrisel presented to him at this miraculous sight of standing upon thin air, when a new wonder began.<br><br>Imladrisel's long shriek took on deepening pitch until it grew so changed that its scream now became the roar of great conflagration. An awakened blast of filial fire risen within it sent a resounding shockwave rushing through the great forest: a hurling wind that blew against the very hand of Time. Windshoal was dismayed, for he understood Imladrisel would flare brightly in dire battle. Never did any blazing sword in Elven memory loose forth eldritch brilliance with a similar vehemence.<br><br>"Am I dead?" Windshoal implored the air around him for answer. Nothing stirred, yet he saw that around him the forest still stood. <br><br>"Imladrisel! Am I slain, what is this unnatural thing which I witness? I beseech you, reveal its purpose to me. I am wholly dismayed that I see my doom is graven upon your wrath."       <br><br>        <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/eq12.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/12/02 6:05:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/28/01 1:51:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Title: just past the next chance right beside an opportu</span><hr size=1> A touch at his shoulder spun him wheeling around, half expecting to face his nameless dread enemy, instead he saw that he looked upon a woodelf maiden clad all in Lambent armor. She impatiently dismissed Imladrisel's roar, as if standing within its holy light was a common sight, which it was, and gave motion to Windshoal to take the sealed note which she took from her satchel. <br><br>His fears forgotten, Windshoal couldn't decide which stunned him more, this maiden's blithe ignorance at Imladrisel's grave sign or the fact that she clearly believed her own singular task, a common one, remained still the more urgent of them. Her note bore the King's Royal Insignia on the parchment wax but surely that could not outweigh this compulsion of The Lady in heaven. <br><br>"Listen, hey look listen, the message is straight from..." began Silvermoss, as politely as she could. <br><br>His frightened glare shot hotly back at her and she noticed the empty scabbard he wore hung at his side. Silvermoss resisted an impulse to throw off the Lambent armor and likewise convince this gaping knight that he must face a calamitous situation. He did not even notice her taller companion.<br><br>"That blade is Imladrisel, a holy sword, young maiden. Do you mean to suppose that the King's bidding must foreswear divine purpose, since heaven itself calls me?" he angrily interjected, indicating at the blazing sword before she had finished.<br><br>"I am honor bound, the SongWeavers will not hear of heroic Elf glory unsung; alas, here I see you are doomed against any hopes of an bright outcome. Heaven certainly purposes that you shall oppose its foe, with your life, typically the price of our sacred mortal struggles. Your sword surely cannot be a trifling thing to ponder." <br><br>Silvermoss stifled the yawn which might have angered him before it escaped.  <br><br>Windshoal was not consoled. He clutched at myriad possibilities. It was true, he may not remain alive once this promise of battle was fulfilled. For now he was grown old. But with small aid he could hope to fight into his final remaining hour. Perhaps this woodelf maid was sent to him for this very purpose. <br><br>"So it was you who always pursued me. I grew aware of your days long pursuit behind. I thought some enemy hunted me." He opened the parchment without more delay and finally commenced to read it.<br><br>"The palace is ransacked..." it began. "Both King and Queen are taken from us to where none may guess the place..." and there he stopped reading, Windshoal knew he could not bear to finish reading more.<br><br>"So this is the meaning of Imladrisel." His voice sobbed, broken inside him came his thudding heartbeat. The parchment fell crumpled from his hand onto the earth. <br><br>Imladrisel flared painfully brighter, it seemed, a brief moment. <br><br>From nowhere a howling wind came rushing at his ears and dizzyness overtook him. His sight sank into a deep darkness and he felt his strength failing him.  <br><br>"I must know what you think to do hereafter, sir. I do not propose to be a mere warmth at your side along the way. My treefolk have abandoned the city, High Elves all march in arms to make war here. I'm sad to say not a single soul has been spared, this matter is perilous indeed." Silvermoss smiled bravely. Windshoal looked sharply back at her. Presence of mind restoring his wits once more. <br><br>The tiny Woodelf plainly had more to say so he nodded dumb consent. Silvermoss, clasping to his elbow for support, now strained her Woodelf's height on tiptoe to gain the reach of his ear. She must officially address him thus, it was his turn to sigh now, for the Royal Seal upon his parchment compelled her salutatory obeisance: from ancient times their formal ceremonial heraldry. <br><br>Though the two Elven peoples resided under one united Elf Kingdom only the woodelf maidens performed a royal court ceremony of tiptoe address, Silvermoss was one. <br><br>In the memory of the Royal Court, a woodelf maid on tiptoe held no other rival for sneaking past company unobserved. Since time immemorial High Elves had cherished the legendary fame of their Queen's loyal train of woodelf handmaidens. In the eyes of the Woodelves themselves, however, the only way to whisper secretly into the ear of a court High Elf is to reach it first. <br><br>This revealed her upbringing among the court nobility to Windshoal, grinning grimly he was impressed. No less than a Royal handmaiden. Queen's Lady-in-Waiting for certain. <br><br>Recognition of her correct Heraldic form of address to a member of the Royal Tunarean court further enlarged Windshoal's own sense of his gathering doom.   <br><br>She continued, whispering in a quavering voice: "There is no question that elves gave themselves into slavery to be with their King. Our slaughter is gruesome, scattered throughout all the Elddar forest are bones of butchered Woodelf maidens, stripped of flesh like so much cattle. Dainty meat commanded to be sent to the shadowy enemy's foul table. <br>I have observed our kindred meekly go to this unholy sacrifice, for their King's sake, and recieve the knife across their throats." <br><br>"They march, perhaps to Nektulos, without any will. None seek escape and they cannot be persuaded otherwise, they do not hear." <br><br>This Silvermoss said matter-of-fact, her voice began sounding broken and dejected as it trailed away. Then finally she was miserably silent and hot tears came streaming down those lovely cheeks. Numbed by the enormity of what she just told him, Windshoal was caught totally unprepared: he did not know what comforting he could offer her. She crumpled in a fallen heap, clinging fast to his legs like a desperate child sobbing at his feet. The road before their kingdom lay heavily upon him.<br><br>   <br>              <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/eq12.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/12/02 8:19:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  P