rely covered her crotch, just as Silvermoss had said. Shining small dewy leaves dusted themselves into a sparkling emerald Circlet which perpetually ringed Feana's  head atop her astonishing silvery hair. Hiding his stare, and not a little admiration with it, Windshoal noticed her eyes too shone brilliant green and how she wore an innocent elvish grin. He felt her bright innocence strongly, Windshoal silently admitted that he felt a goodly liking for the girl.<br><br>"I am curious still to hear why she does not cover her breasts. I had thought this was the common fashion of people." He told Silvermoss this privately. The answer though did not surprise him.<br><br>"Feana was cast out from her mother's folk still a tender babe - because of her strange Elvish birth. Her mother did not teach her to dress but to live. The Druid maiden walks alone throughout the forest attending to the great trees and wild creatures. When Druids came upon Feana wandering and alone, in the wilderness, and found her thus naked, they immediately claimed her guardianship for the Lady Tunare of Heaven.  <br><br>"Moreover of her protection even the Barbarian Goddess, Marr herself, declares Feana singularly inviolable, thereby heaven recognises in the father's kindred the race of Elves. Thus Feana astonished the forest: the Druids correctly proclaimed Feana is a sacred trust upon all of the Elves, in the name of Tunare, Mother of All... <br>"It's a long story, Feana is blessed by the Gods. Young just as she appears now, ever naked, unchanged. First living of her new race to walk Norrath: all heaven is clamouring over her. Mother Tunare has granted this responsibility to the Elves." <br><br>"Behold!, maidenhood is not lightly sullied." trilled Silvermoss sternly... No longer bound by any formalities of their Court her patience had at last stretched thin.  <br><br>She snatched up Windshoal's arm. Thrusting his hand upon Feana's bosom. Instantly, the sear of tearing flesh burned in his hand and he let out an involuntary yelp. Looking anxiously at his hastily withdrawn hand he saw that it was freshly scored with some deep scratches. Windshoal felt his face redden, and the two fae women studied his burning complexion with a fascination in their gazes which made his face burn even more.   <br><br>"Feana has said.." began Silvermoss, clearly not done with Windshoal yet. <br><br>Translating for Feana, she continued speaking to him, "Imladrisel's sign is not as fatal as you imagine. Therefore do not dismay, holy knight. This sign is a beacon to the Elves. All can see it." <br><br>Apparently, Feana understood his own tongue! Windshoal did not ask if the half-elf child could also speak it, he reasoned that Feana must deliberately wish this secret kept.    <br><br>"Here finally is an Elvish host which had sought some sign to follow", Silvermoss ended. Now Windshoal looked and saw that Feana pointed to a gathering company of Elven knights newly-grown around them. The keener senses of the two maidens detected these latest Elves arriving before he was aware of their approach.  <br><br>Brightly armored Paladins kept their gazes averted from the naked Druid, and they drew even more distance from Feana when one, an unwitting female in the company, again demonstrated Feana's invisible guardian: a shield of thorns. The proud Paladin glumly nursed deep scratches on her newly bleeding hand. <br><br>She clutched Feana's wrist meaning kindly to take the maiden aside, and find her some clothing. At the shrugs of her male companions she glared, it appeared clear to them that there might soon come quarrelsome blows and so they wisely rummaged around in their packs. Fully over a hundred more elf women Paladins among their party stood behind her, glaring likewise at the knightly elves about them. From then onwards, no High Elf ever spoke uttering comments against Feana's apparent choice in dress or made joke at her uncustomarily bared breasts. In the vast Elddar forest more strange things had served clever minds and hands for their owner's rainment. <br>         <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.bigpond.com/dwmac/eq12.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/12/02 8:22:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/5/01 5:39:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Title: just past the next chance right beside an opportu</span><hr size=1> The Elven host assembled into ranks before the command had been ordered and busied itself with preparations for battle. Amid the din and clattering of metal armor Imladrisel's roar ran through Elves like an intonation of purpose. Windshoal knew with certainty he must decide how to lead his army into battle against their enemy before he dare hold the sword, Imladrisel, aloft. <br><br>Windshoal's brows knotted, he had been feverishly planning their assault even as he left appointed officers to carry out the first task of discovering his army's strengths and numbers. It was obvious to him now that the sword would reveal which direction their next course lay once he determined to wield it and do battle. He came to the place he had left fiery Imladrisel still flaming and found the holy sword surrounded by a throng of robed Elves. Amidst this group Feana spoke in her strange tongue solemnly nodding her head now and then. Some debate between them was apparently settled. Feana turned to face Windshoal, now she spoke addressing him directly in Elder Elvish.<br><br>"Noble Knight, the sign of Imladrisel is clear to all Elven lore, not least of it to magic and enchantment. None that see this sacred sight shall know rest. None shall put aside the path you must set upon us now to save their people and find your King. It is certain, by such a grave token the Elves will never return to this ancient forest wholly unopposed and ever again see their great city still standing proud." <br><br>Feana did not smile. Something about their dispassionate gloom disturbed him, another burden that lay upon Feana which she did not name. Windshoal guessed that the Druid maiden shared her secret knowledge when she spoke her own tongue to these robed Elves.              <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A> at: 11/18/01 4:57:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www..\program files\everquest\eq000013b.gif WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/15/01 9:10:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Title: just past the next chance right beside an opportu</span><hr size=1> The gathering numbers of Elves drawn by Imladrisel's light swelled their host to thousands.  Windshoal saw with grim satisfaction many Woodelf faces, armed with terrible determination and Eldritch bows. They came ready for war, with a truly awesome speed, swift as silent arrows, deadly purpose was written in their eyes. Woodelf Rangers, forest people skilled both in sword and bow came to fight in their forest home.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udhariana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dhariana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/1/01 10:07:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Title: just past the next chance right beside an opportu</span><hr size=1> When do we get more of this story??  I've been waiting forever now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Dhariana Skincrawler<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/trueallegiance">&lt;True Allegiance&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/18/01 7:48:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Title: just past the next chance right beside an opportu</span><hr size=1> Now the Elves arraigned their number into troops, again without another's bidding for each elf knew his and her singular task. Thousands of glittering swords shone against the bright fire of Imladrisel and in amongst the gleaming Elven ranks shone the short swords of Rangers not least - though the stark woodelfs held their great bows ready now.<br><br>Beyond Imladrisel ran a small stream, here before it the vast Elven host recieved great power from all spells of Eldritch arcane lore which their knowledge possessed: Heroism, Runes, Regrowth, Shield of Words, and many more were the deeds of magick wrought around the host. Windshoal saw that with their power at its fullest it was time he lay hold of Imladrisel, and to begin the fury of his assault. <br><br>Muttering obeisance to Tunare on bended knee, Windshoal rose and in full sense of grim war set his hands firmly gripped upon the sword Imladrisel. With that act ten thousand flaming swords flashed in unison. He saw that the Elves likewise all similarly had prayed to the Lady even as he did so himself.  <br><br>Now there was wonder in them, for their sight saw beyond their beloved Elddar forest across a seperate Plane of their world. A window into nether-space lay revealed to the Elves, in it a road ran before them. Enclosed on all sides by solid rock. The robed Elves murmured spells of power, some wove binding incantations but they stayed their ground, there came a nodding murmur of recognition at their newest revelation within the light of Imladrisel's power. <br><br>Seeing no sign from them to delay longer Windshoal and the army of Paladins surged forward sounding their battle roar.<br><br>Behind him, Windshoal knew the Woodelf Rangers already sensed their enemy, indeed even Silvermoss. Now she beat a chanting song of battle for the whole company on her Selos drum which brought the hot blood rushing through him, their strength rising, unnatural speed hastening them. <br><br>Far ahead he thought he recognised disciples of Hate, though he was at a loss to know what brought the unnatural beings to assemble armed against captive Elves. At once, a din of fighting appeared to set the Elves against each other but Imladrisel screamed anew, and the eyes of entraced Woodelves long captive in this place were opened. <br><br>They ran swiftly in their thousands past the knights and quickly gained their freedom behind the safe protection of the Rangers. An unnatural power suddenly gripped the Elves, cold malice washed them, then from out of the ground a horde of rats came. Rats quickly fevered and weakened elves that held firm against this attack but their evil lord did not reckon with the deadly aim of Woodelf archers, nor the power of the holy knights. The rats were quickly put asunder. <br><br>Silvermoss saw Windshoal and his Paladins raging further up ahead now brought their terrifying battle everywhere, against ever greater foes, and the shouts of bloody fighting was in deadly earnest. <br>Dark elf-like creatures, a huge Dracoliche she thought resembled in its terrible onset the fearsome dragons. Dreamlike she saw they all heard the barking doom of immortal Tashani. She saw them glance nervously about. Even discomforted and knowing fully that their resistance to Elvish magic was gone, the dark foe came at them still, unworldly bedlam swarmed over the battle from every side. The fall of furious Elves ran like an icy tide, some withstanding the insidious embrace of dark malice but not the evilly poisonous humor of their sudden wounds. <br><br>Fellow knights rose undaunted beside them and laid their healing upon the dying. Yet their own plight was plainly as dire. Over it uproar came from all around upon the ears of Silvermoss, everywhere she turned she saw total pandemonium and its shocking sight revealed by the light of Imladrisel shivered her company of Woodelves.  <br><br>Now Silvermoss saw that the mysterious robed elves made an assault of magicks, great fiery blasts that shook the Dracoliche. A mighty shock of magical Swords lacerated it, wounding it further, and in every direction she looked a deadly rain of arrows fell on ruined enemy.  Starfire and Scoriae roared, Lightning blasts thundered, Feana must surely be here as well. The magical destruction of Tears of Druzzil seared the black shade of Hate and shrivelled his sea of disciples, Silvermoss realised with a terrible chill that here where she stood the entire remainder of the elven people fought and were dying. <br><br>Even just now hundreds of shining High Elves were flung horribly asunder from their fighting at one cruel blow of a titanic fisted paw, they lay still never stirring again. Then she saw Windshoal, blinding bright against the vast monstrous dark shape. <br><br>The others could not reach him.<br><br>The titanic fist of Hate only struck a glancing blow against the others, for Innoruk battered him with terrible and savage force directly, armor did not withstand the brutal power of this unnatural being's spite. Silvermoss saw Windshoal stood his ground all broken inside and he fought on stubbornly.                         <br><br>    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=misty>Misty</A> at: 12/2/01 10:25:52 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showPrevMessage?topicID=146.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showNextMessage?topicID=146.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=146.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.emailToFriend?topicID=146.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplaying.threadControl?topicID=146.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplayin